OL,3,CPeople 'living shorter lives than they
OL,4,Cshould' due to austerity and cuts
OL,6,FPeople in England are "suffering
OL,7,Favoidable ill-health and living
OL,8,Fshorter lives than they should" due to
OL,9,Fausterity and cuts to essential
OL,10,Fservices, new analysis shows.
OL,12,FNew analysis, by academics from the
OL,13,FInstitute of Health Equity at
OL,14,FUniversity College London (UCL), found
OL,15,Fpeople's health has deteriorated,
OL,16,Fhealth inequalities have widened, and
OL,17,Fthe north-south health gap has
OL,18,Fincreased.
