OL,3,CPeople 'living shorter lives than they
OL,4,Cshould' due to austerity and cuts
OL,6,F"It is no surprise that local
OL,7,Fauthorities are struggling to make
OL,8,Fends meet and that people are living
OL,9,Fshorter lives than they should," Sir
OL,10,FMichael wrote.
OL,12,F"If you slash the services that
OL,13,Fsupport people then health will be
OL,14,Fharmed. Levelling up was supposed to
OL,15,Fprovide badly-needed funding for the
OL,16,Fmost deprived areas. But it was a
OL,17,Fderisory amount and, as a result,
OL,18,Fnever going to improve health."
OL,20,FKey findings from the new report
OL,21,Finclude:
