OL,6,FAt a regional level, north-east
OL,7,FEngland saw the biggest gap in life
OL,8,Fexpectancy between the least deprived
OL,9,Fand most deprived neighbourhoods in
OL,10,F2017-19, at 12.2 years for males and
OL,11,F9.7 years for females, followed by
OL,12,Fnorth-west England (11.3 and 9.6 years
OL,13,Frespectively) and Yorkshire & the
OL,14,FHumber (10.4 and 8.5 years).
OL,16,FThe regions with the lowest inequality
OL,17,Fwere all in the south: London (7.2
OL,18,Fyears for males and 5.1 for females),
OL,19,Fthe South West (7.5 and 5.6 years
OL,20,Frespectively) and the South East (7.8
OL,21,Fand 6.1 years).
